INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '7bb981b7-27a7-46ea-b5c3-8a5be7bfbd9b',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Astro View Transitions — Page Animations and Layout Persistence Without a SPA$escape$,
  $escape$Astro's View Transitions API ships as a first-class component via `astro:transitions`. Drop `<ViewTransitions />` into your layout's `<head>` and Astro converts every MPA navigation into an animated, SPA-like page swap — zero client JS bundle overhead required.

Shared-element morphs use `transition:name`. Give the same name to a matching element on both pages and the browser interpolates position, size, and opacity automatically. Astro bundles four `transition:animate` presets — `fade`, `slide`, `morph`, and `none` — all overridable with a custom `AnimationBuilder` or raw CSS `@keyframes`.

For components that must survive navigation intact — audio players, scroll position, form state — `transition:persist` prevents DOM teardown. The node is physically moved into the incoming page rather than destroyed and remounted, preserving in-memory React/Svelte/Vue state.

Programmatic navigation goes through `navigate()` from `astro:transitions/client`. For side effects, listen to `document` lifecycle events: `astro:before-preparation` (intercept), `astro:after-preparation` (modify DOM before swap), and `astro:after-swap` (reinitialize third-party widgets). Browsers without View Transitions support fall back to normal navigation — no polyfill needed.$escape$,
  $escape$---
// Layout.astro
import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions';
const { post } = Astro.props;
---
<head>
  <ViewTransitions />
</head>

<!-- Shared-element morph: same name on source and destination page -->
<img src={post.cover} transition:name={`hero-${post.slug}`} transition:animate="morph" />

<!-- Sidebar survives navigation — React state preserved -->
<aside transition:persist="sidebar">
  <AudioPlayer client:load />
</aside>$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
